"releaseNotes":"New — MTR (My Traceroute)\nCombines ping and traceroute into one continuous live view. Discovers every hop to your destination then probes each one every second, showing packet loss percentage, last, average, and best latency per hop — just like the classic MTR tool.\n\nNew — Certificate Expiry Tracker\nAdd any domain and NetSleuth fetches its SSL certificate and tracks days until expiry. Color-coded warnings at 30 and 14 days. Domains persist between sessions. Tap any entry to re-check. Swipe to remove.\n\nNew — Copy on Tap\nLong press any result in Ping, Traceroute, or DNS Lookup to copy it to your clipboard instantly.\n\nNew — Subnet Calculator\nEnter any IP and CIDR prefix to instantly calculate network address, broadcast, first/last host, subnet mask, wildcard, usable host count, IP class, and binary mask. Built-in subnet splitter breaks any network into 2, 4, 8, or 16 subnets.\n\nNew — LAN Scanner\nDiscovers active devices on your local WiFi network. Shows IP, hostname, response time, and flags your device and gateway.\n\nNew — TLS Inspector\nTests TLS 1.0–1.3 support, shows cipher suites, certificate details, HSTS status, HTTP/2 support, and gives your server an overall grade from A+ to F.\n\nWiFi Info — Rebuilt\nNow shows real connection data including connection type, IPv4/IPv6 support, Low Data Mode status, expensive connection flag, local IPv4 and IPv6 addresses, and WiFi security type — all 100% real data, nothing estimated. Signal strength (dBm) has been removed as Apple restricts access to this data from App Store apps.", "version":"1.4", "wrapperType":"software", "currency":"USD", 
"description":"NetSleuth is a powerful network diagnostic toolkit for iPhone and iPad. Whether you're a developer, IT professional, or just someone who wants to understand what's happening on their network, NetSleuth gives you professional-grade tools in one clean, fast app.\n\n* Speed Test\nMeasures your connection the way it should be measured. Tests download, upload, latency, jitter, loaded latency, and packet loss — then gives you a Bufferbloat Grade (A–F) showing how your connection performs under real load. Powered by Cloudflare.\n\n* Ping\nPing any host with a single burst or continuous mode. Watch latency in real time on a live scrolling graph with color-coded results and timeout detection.\n\n* Traceroute\nTrace the full path to any host with live reverse DNS lookups showing real router and infrastructure hostnames at every hop.\n\n* DNS Lookup\nQuery A, AAAA, MX, TXT, CNAME, and NS records for any domain.\n\n* DNS Propagation\nCheck if your domain has propagated across 10 major DNS servers worldwide including Google, Cloudflare, Quad9, and AdGuard.\n\n* DNS over HTTPS (DoH)\nTest whether your device is using encrypted DNS. Checks 6 major DoH providers and estimates your protection level.\n\n* Port Checker\nScan common ports on any host to see what's open or closed.\n\n* WHOIS\nLook up domain registration and ownership details instantly.\n\n* SSL Inspector\nInspect SSL/TLS certificates — view issuer, validity dates, and days until expiry.\n\n* WiFi Info\nSee your local IP, external IP, subnet, gateway, and DNS. Enable location permission to reveal signal strength in dBm, SSID, BSSID, and channel with 2.4/5 GHz detection.\n\n* IP Info\nGeolocate any IP address with a map view, ISP, timezone, region, and coordinates.\n\nNo ads. No account required. No data collected.", "userRatingCountForCurrentVersion":0, "userRatingCount":0}, 
